    <main class="main-panel">
      <div class="page-header-area">
        <h1 class="page-title">Color</h1>
        <p class="page-desc">Use color to create meaning, reinforce trust, and accelerate operational decisions across endpoint workflows.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="main-content-area">
        <div class="main-content-inner">

          <!-- Intro -->
          <div class="doc-section" style="margin-top: 16px;">
            <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--prism-text-muted); max-width: 760px;">In Prism, color is not decorative. It communicates system health, risk severity, action priority, device state, policy compliance, and workflow confidence.</p>
            <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--prism-text-muted); max-width: 760px; margin-top: 12px;">A strong color system helps admins scan faster, reduce mistakes, and act safely under pressure.</p>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Color anatomy -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="color-anatomy" class="doc-section-title">Color anatomy</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Prism color foundation follows three layers.</p>

            <h3 id="saturated-colors" class="doc-h3">Saturated colors</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Used for meaning-rich UI signals.</p>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 12px; margin-top: 16px;">
              <div style="padding: 16px; border-radius: 10px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                <div style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Critical threat alerts</div>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 16px; border-radius: 10px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                <div style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Successful remediation</div>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 16px; border-radius: 10px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                <div style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Warning states</div>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 16px; border-radius: 10px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                <div style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Brand CTAs</div>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 16px; border-radius: 10px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                <div style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Active navigation</div>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 16px; border-radius: 10px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                <div style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">AI recommendation highlights</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <h3 id="neutral-colors" class="doc-h3">Neutral colors</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Used for structural UI: backgrounds, surfaces, borders, tables, dividers, secondary text, disabled states, and empty states. Neutrals must support both dense light and dark environments.</p>

            <h3 id="alpha-colors" class="doc-h3">Alpha colors</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Transparent overlays used for adaptive surfaces: hover overlays, selected rows, focus rings, drawer scrims, severity heatmap overlays, and live telemetry pulse layers. Alpha colors must adapt safely across elevations and themes.</p>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Token-first color system -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="token-system" class="doc-section-title">Token-first color system</h2>
            <div style="margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; background: rgba(220,38,38,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(220,38,38,0.12); border-radius: 12px;">
              <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;"><strong>Never use raw HEX values in Prism products.</strong> All colors must be applied through semantic tokens.</p>
            </div>

            <h3 id="token-structure" class="doc-h3">Token structure</h3>
            <div style="margin-top: 16px; padding: 20px 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-violet); line-height: 2;">
              color.{property}.{role}.{emphasis}.{state}
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 12px;">Collection: <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:12px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">UEMS Theme Tokens</code> &middot; Supports light &amp; dark mode switching</p>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

